{
  "texts": [
    "This approach aligns with the idea of training in adaptive environments, which has been previously explored by adjusting prompts during training (Zeng et al., 2025).",
    "In contrast, we adapt the environment by updating the verifier (rubrics).",
    "Future work may consider jointly adapting both prompts and rubric criteria to further improve training efficiency.",
    "A new dimension of scaling verifier compute: providing more privileged information to the judge.",
    "Another perspective on RLER is that it creates a new way to scale the compute used by the verifier."
  ]
}